        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Add Extra Lines to Define Extended Item Descriptions | Microsoft Docs</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>You can add extra lines to extend the standard text that describes an item.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Add Extended Item Text</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can extend a standard text for items by adding extra lines, and you can set up conditions for use of the extra lines.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You do this from item cards.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To define extended text for an item description</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Open the card for an item that you want to add extended text to, and then choose the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Extended Text<ept id="p1">**</ept> action.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Fill in the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Code<ept id="p1">**</ept> and <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Description<ept id="p2">**</ept> fields.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Choose the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>New<ept id="p1">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Fill in the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Language Code<ept id="p1">**</ept> field or select the <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>All Language Codes<ept id="p2">**</ept> check box if you use language codes.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Fill in the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Starting Date<ept id="p1">**</ept> and <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Ending Date<ept id="p2">**</ept> fields if you want to limit the dates on which the extended text is used.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Text<ept id="p1">**</ept> field, write the extended text.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select relevant check boxes for the document types where you want the extended text printed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Close the page.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To add an extended item text on a sales order line</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Open a sales order with a sales line for an item that has extended text defined.</source>
